                            <comment id="13277576" author="hustlmsp" created="Thu, 17 May 2012 06:14:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;thanks Aniruddha. the patch seems good. just one comment, sees that AVAILABLE_NODE spreads over several files. could we consider moving it to a common place (which could be shared by client and server), such as AbstractConfiguration to have a method getAvailableBookiesPath(), which is similar what Hedwig did in ServerConfiguration to manage its znode path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278436" author="i0exception" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 01:03:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reviewing. I have updated the patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278503" author="hustlmsp" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 03:05:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Aniruddha for quick response.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;sorry that I don&apos;t explain it more clearly. it would be better to have a method #getZkAvailableBookiesPath().&lt;br/&gt;
so user doesn&apos;t need to write code as below &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.bookieRegistrationPath = conf.getZkLedgersRootPath() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + conf.getBookiesAvailableNode();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;instead, they could write code as&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.bookieRegistrationPath = conf.getZkAvailableBookiesPath();
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in AbstractionConfiguration, &apos;available&apos; could be defined as a constant value, and do string concatenation in method #getZkAvailableBookiesPath().&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; AVAILABLE_ZNODE = &apos;available&apos;;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; getZkAvailableBookiesPath() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; getZkLedgersRootPath() + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + AVAILABLE_ZNODE;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;seems it could make the code clearer. How is your opinion?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13278624" author="i0exception" created="Fri, 18 May 2012 08:13:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, now it&apos;s clearer. I&apos;ve updated the patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13279982" author="hustlmsp" created="Mon, 21 May 2012 07:27:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;the patch is pretty good to me. +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
